{{Infobox scientist |name = Petrus Ryff |image = |image_size = |caption = |birth_date = May 8, 1552 |birth_place = [[Basel]], [[Swiss Confederacy]] |death_date = May 19, 1629 |death_place = Basel, Swiss Confederacy |residence = |citizenship = |nationality = Swiss |fields = |workplaces = |alma_mater = [[University of Basel]] (M.D. 1584) |thesis_title = De affectibus cordis |thesis_url = http://www.e-rara.ch/doi/10.3931/e-rara-133 |thesis_year = 1584 |doctoral_advisor = [[Felix Plater]]<ref>[http://neurotree.org/neurotree/peopleinfo.php?pid=23267 Petrus Ryff's Neurotree profile]</ref> |academic_advisors = |doctoral_students = [[Emmanuel Stupanus]] |known_for = |influences = [[Theodor Zwinger]] |influenced = |awards = }} '''Petrus Ryff''' (<small>Swiss</small> {{IPA-de|rif|lang}}; {{lang-la|Petrus Ryffius}}; May 8, 1552 – May 19, 1629) was a [[Switzerland|Swiss]] [[mathematics|mathematician]], [[physician]] and [[chronicle]]r from [[Basel]].
== Life and work == Petrus Ryff was born in [[Basel]], [[Swiss Confederacy|Switzerland]]. He was the son of Daniel Ryff (1529–1612), and Ursula Zimmermann,<ref>{{cite web | last = Stroux | first = Ulrich | title = Genealogie der Familie Stroux - Speiser | url = http://www.stroux.org/patriz_f/stQV_f/Rf_f.pdf | accessdate = 10 December 2008 }}</ref> and the grandnephew of Basler chronicler [[Fridolin Ryff]].
Petrus Ryff enrolled in the University of his hometown in 1569; he received the [[Baccalaureus]] in 1572 and the ''[[Master of Philosophy|Magister Philosophiae]]'' degree in 1576. He continued to study Medicine, following the lectures of [[Theodor Zwinger]], [[Thomas Erastus]], [[Felix Plater]], and [[Johann Nicolaus Stupanus]]. He was awarded the degree of [[Doctor of Medicine|Medical Doctor]] in 1584. After that he practiced medicine for a few years, until he succeeded [[Christian Wursteisen]] as Professor of Mathematics at the [[University of Basel]] in 1586, a position he held until his death in 1629. In 1596 he became a Consultant of the School of Medicine, where he was an active member and 7 times Dean.<ref>{{cite book |last= Miescher |first= Friedrich |title= Die Medizinische Facultät in Basel und ihr Aufschwung unter F. Plater und C. Bauhin, mit dem Lebensbilde von Felix Plater |publisher= Schweighauser |year= 1860 | location= Basel | pages= 28 | url= https://books.google.com/books?id=vywJAAAAIAAJ&pg=PA14#PPA28,M1 | oclc= 245533138 }}</ref>
He was the author of several books of mathematics, astronomy, and astrology. Among the last is a prognostication for 1594.<ref>{{cite book |last= Thorndike |first= Lynn |title= A History of Magic and Experimental Science: Volumes V and VI, the Sixteenth Century |publisher= [[Columbia University Press]] |year= 1943 | isbn= 0-231-08795-0 | url=https://books.google.com/books?id=cgKm55wQMGUC&printsec=frontcover&source=gbs_summary_r&cad=0#PPA143,M1 |pages= 143 |chapter=Chapter XXXIII Astrology after 1550 }}</ref> However, Petrus Ryff is best remembered for continuing and publishing the Basler Chronicles his granduncle Fridolin Ryff maintained between 1514 and 1541.<ref>{{cite book | last = Vischer | first = Wilhelm |author2=Alfred Stern | title = Basler Chroniken | publisher = Hirzel, Historische und Antiquarische Gesellschaft zu Basel | year = 1872 | location = Leipzig | pages = 13 | url = https://books.google.com/books?id=G7YBAAAAYAAJ&pg=PA13#PPA13,M1 | oclc= 19455191 }}</ref><ref>{{cite book | last = Thommen | first = Rudolf | title = Geschichte der Universität Basel, 1532-1632 | publisher = C. Detloffs | year = 1889 | location = Basel | pages = 279 | url = https://books.google.com/books?id=uOYMAAAAYAAJ&pg=PA221#PPA279,M1 | oclc= 3548482 }}</ref> After Fridolin died the chronicles were bequeathed to his daughter Magdalena, who passed them on to Petrus Ryff. He continued the chronicles from 1543–1585, and in 1585 he published the chronicles. The ''Basler Chroniken'' were edited and re-published in 1872 by the ''Historische und Antiquarische Gesellschaft zu Basel''. They provide an invaluable source of information about the history of Basel, and that part of Europe in the 16th century.
== Selected works == *[https://dx.doi.org/10.3931/e-rara-133 ''De affectibus cordis''], disputatio. Basel: 1584. [[Online Computer Library Center|OCLC]] [http://worldcat.org/oclc/165706088 165706088] *[http://www.e-rara.ch/doi/10.3931/e-rara-186 ''De externis corporis vitiis velitatio medica'']. Basel: 1584 *''Historiam Basiliensem'', quam patruus ejus ''Fridolinus Ryff'', senator ac scholarcha, a primordiis urbis inceptam & ad sue usque tempora protactum reliquit, ab a. 1514 ad vitae suae terminum continuatit, qua vero hactenus non fuit edita. Basel: 1585. *''Sphaera mundi : hoc est, Elementa cosmographiae, legibus logicis, in usum Acad. Basiliensis'', Basel: 1593. [[Online Computer Library Center|OCLC]] [http://worldcat.org/oclc/258505324 258505324] *''Quaestiones geometricae, in Euclidis et P. Rami - Quibus geodesiam adjecimus per usum radii geometrici'', Frankfurt: 1600. [[Online Computer Library Center|OCLC]] [http://worldcat.org/oclc/60916808 60916808] *''Compendium arithmeticae Vrstisii'', Oxford: 1627 *''Editio Altera, cui accessit Commentatio Optica, sive brevis Tractatio de Perspectiva Communi'', Oxford: 1665
